subSubSection.paragraph:
Remarks
This ovigerous male specimens was identified as 

A. eroticus

based on the second coxae of all legs with ventrally long spurs, the lateral processes with short spines, a small but distally erect cement gland duct, and the femurs without spurs (
Stock 1968
; 
Arango & Maxmen 2006
; 
Lucena & Christoffersen 2018b
).
